content.description: Locate the obvious circular rock scar on the route Hollow Man, and search for two left leaning crimps about 30 feet to the left. Use them to pull the committing first moves up onto the slab, proceed upward on tiny crystals.
A fun climb, but the holds are SUPER sharp. Would definitely rate 3 stars if the holds were just a little more comfortable. Start matched on a good undercling and move up and right to a hollow flake.
content.location: This is the most obvious line on Hollywood Wall. Look for the big circular rock scar about 80 feet to the left of where Hollywood Wall disappears into Main Dome.

content.description: Thin moves at the start and then slab climbing to the top! Start on a good crimp and then make your way up.
content.location: This problem starts about 50 left of where Hollywood Wall disappears into the dome. A very small, leftward leaning seam is just to the right of the climb.

content.description: This overlap high up on Main Dome has a couple problems worth doing if you happen to be in the area. This prominint feature is visible from the road if you are driving to the park from the north.
